com.ibm.team.repository.common

Interface IConfigurationData


  • public interface IConfigurationData
    IConfigurationData is ConfigurationAware data managing Configuration specific data of the COnfiguraiton for a specific item state.

      • createSetIgnoredAndInternal

        IConfigurationData createSetIgnoredAndInternal(boolean ignored,
                                               boolean internal)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. If using to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are not provided by this method and it is recommended to use a different ConfigurationData call.. This method explicitly copies the configurationData while setting the ignored and internal attributes, as a convenience method

      • createCopy

        IConfigurationData createCopy()
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. If using to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are not provided by this method and it is recommended to use a different ConfigurationData call.. If IConfigurationData parameter is null, the created IConfigurationData will have a changeSetId UUID NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT. This method explicitly copies the configurationData as a convenience method
        Parameters:
        configurationData -
        Returns:
        configurationData
